data.description: Nestled off Purcell Blvd between Hwy 50 and I25, this Pueblo West rancher seamlessly blends curb appeal with contemporary features, creating a haven of comfort and style. As you step in, expansive living areas greet you, defined by vaulted ceilings that add an airy and open ambiance. Central air conditioning ensures comfort throughout the seasons, and a charming fireplace in the dining area becomes the heart of the home—a perfect spot for gatherings and relaxation.  The master suite stands as a tranquil retreat, boasting a luxurious soaking tub and direct access to the rear patio, providing a secluded space for relaxation and connection with the outdoors. For RV owners, the property is thoughtfully equipped with 220 power, adding an extra layer of convenience to accommodate various lifestyle needs. Situated on an acre, the backyard is a versatile canvas, fully fenced for pet security and offering an ideal space for a myriad of outdoor activities.  Evenings under the stars can be enjoyed around the firepit, while the heavy-duty shed with its adjacent concrete slab adds versatility for storage or creative projects. Exciting updates enhance the property's allure, including a newer roof, septic tank, and the thoughtful addition of a solar package. This solar package significantly boosts energy efficiency, resulting in an impressive 99% reduction in costs while contributing to environmental sustainability.
